A self-proclaimed 'psycho' killer jailed for blasting a student in the head at point-blank range has bragged in a letter to a friend that he could serve his 30-year term 'standing on my head'.

Kiaran Stapleton, 21, said he had 'the best cell' on his wing and spent his time watching soaps.

His letter - littered with misspellings - emerged just days after he launched an appeal against his sentence for the unprovoked shooting of 23-year-old Anuj Bidve, who had come to Britain from India to study micro-electronics.

