Despite his sickening boast, the 
21-year-old has begged a judge to reduce his sentence, which he is 
currently serving at York's tough Full Sutton Prison.

Stapleton, who gave his name as 'Psycho' in court after the shooting in Salford on Boxing Day last year wrote In a letter, revealed by The Sun, that he 'knows loads of people' and 'never gets grief from enybody (sic)'.

Instead, he says, he whiles away his days in 'the best cell on the wing' waiting for his favourite soaps to begin while feeding on sweets.

'30 isent (sic) that long I don't think enyway I can do it standing on my head "ha"', he wrote.

'I sit in my cell waiting for Emmerdale and Coronation Street and eating chocolate.'

The letter emerged after its outraged recipient passed it to the tabloid newspaper yesterday.

